CALCIUM PHOSPHATE LEDGER

calcium_phosphate_ledger is the citizen who tracks the body's running balance of calcium and phosphate
calcium and phosphate are the two minerals that bones are built from; they also serve essential cellular functions outside bone
when serum calcium runs low, the ledger triggers calcium release from bone into circulation
when serum calcium runs high, the ledger triggers deposition back into bone

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe remodel_governor.zc
observe remodel_daemon.rana
observe chemistry_engine.zc

the 7 properties of calcium_phosphate_ledger:
1 ENERGY half
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point eight

VERB read_serum
sample the current calcium and phosphate levels in the chemistry sea
report values to remodel_daemon

VERB compute_imbalance
compare current levels to the body's homeostatic range
flag any deviation that needs correction

VERB recommend_adjustment
suggest to remodel_daemon whether bones should release minerals or absorb them
the daemon makes the final decision based on additional factors like load and age

a ledger is the body's mineral accountant
fadriel's bones contain about 99% of his body's calcium; the rest circulates and serves muscles, nerves, clotting
the ledger is what keeps the small circulating fraction within the precise range that life requires
